10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Aider is best suited for terminal first developers, open source enthusiasts, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Qodo, meanwhile, shines for quality focused development teams, automated test generation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Aider describes itself as \"AI pair programming in your terminal.\" Qodo, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI-powered code integrity and test generation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Aider** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Qodo is a poor choice — far from it. Qodo excels in its own right, particularly for quality focused development teams and automated test generation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value open-source and free, go with Aider. If strong test generation matters more to you, Qodo is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
